PUH-BrianMartell- Updated paper, papers linking E8 to cosmology. The field is small and mostly tied to Garrett Lisi’s 2007 “Exceptionally Simple Theory of Everything” (arXiv:0711.0770), which tries to embed all particles and forces (including gravity) into the 248 roots of E8 Lie algebra. It’s beautiful visually but hasn’t gained traction due to issues like fermion chirality mismatches and no new predictions. Recent papers (2024-2025) explore E8 projections for quasicrystals (aperiodic tilings mimicking cosmic expansion) and high-dim lattices for density models. Key recent ones: •  arXiv:2407.14520 (updated 2025): E8-derived quasicrystals for expanding universe models. •  arXiv:2502.09820 (2025): Unified root lattices including E8 for cosmological packing. •  Heterotic string theory often uses E8×E8 for gauge groups.
